OL,6,FHe has pleaded not guilty to the
OL,7,Fcharge.
OL,9,FIn August last year, the Independent
OL,10,FOffice for Police Conduct (IOPC)
OL,11,Fconcluded that a South Wales Police
OL,12,Fofficer should face a hearing into
OL,13,Fgross misconduct "over the accuracy of
OL,14,Faccounts he provided to colleagues
OL,15,Fafter the collision incident".
OL,17,FIts investigation has however found no
OL,18,Findication of contact between the
OL,19,Fpolice vehicle and the boys' e-bike
OL,20,Fimmediately before the collision.
