OL,6,FIt said the officer had a case to
OL,7,Fanswer regarding his driving and
OL,8,Flanguage to the boys at the scene of
OL,9,Fthe collision, adding that his driving
OL,10,Fat the time might have been "outside
OL,11,Fhis level of training and authority"
OL,12,Fand against College of Policing rules.
OL,14,FThe IOPC said the panel might find
OL,15,F"inconsistencies and evidential
OL,16,Fconflicts" in the officer's
OL,17,Finformation which would breach police
OL,18,Fstandards of honesty and integrity.
